제주의 돌담을 형상화하는 이색적이면서도 감각적인 거실은 다들 너무 넓다고 칭찬일색입니다.
침실은 침대용파레트와 함께 매트를 올려놓았습니다. 혹시나 침대에서 떨어져도 안전하답니다.
침실의 창은 블라인드를 설치하여 좀 더 산뜻한 느낌을 제공하려고 애를 써 보았습니다.
욕실 또한 분리형으로 제공하여, 청결을 우선으로 생각하고 만들었습니다. 주방과 같은 타일을 이어감으로써 통일된 인테리어를 제공하고 있습니다.
거실의 끝을 허하게 냅두는것보다 제주스러움을 조금은 더 표현할 수 있는 것을 찾아보고, 옛스런 느낌에 자연스러움을 더해보려는 인테리어로 마감을 해보았습니다.
야외수영장은 공용수영장으로 썬베드를 설치하였습니다. 멀리 보이는 제제기오름을 바라보는 태닝과 물놀이는 더없는 여유를 드릴 것입니다.
특급호텔은 아니지만, 그래도 최소한의 편의를 제공하는것이 저희의 욕심입니다.
큰도로에서 바라다보는 저희 공간입니다. 앞에는 작은 계곡이라 방해할 수 있는 건물이 하나도 없습니다. (아싸아~)
총 3가지의 타입으로 구성되어 있으며, 10객실로 이루어져 그 어떤 리조트나 호텔보다 프라이빗하고 조용하게 지낼 수 있습니다. 모든 공간에 테라스가 있습니다. 밤에 5월에 피는 감귤꽃향기, 9월이나 10월의 제주공기는 그 어떤 지역보다도 싱그러운것 같습니다.

모든 객실은 앞에서보면 2층으로 시작되지만 뒷공간 주차장과 이어진 객실은 1층으로 시작됩니다.
주차장에서 차를 세우시고 카페로 오시면 체크인안내를 도와드리겠습니다.

Links komt u met een klein trapje het terras op. Vervolgens komt u de Shepherd's hut binnen via de openslaande deuren. Vanaf het terras kunt u genieten van de ondergaande zon.

U kunt parkeren op de speciaal voor u gereserveerde parkeerplek. Via het Drentse keienpad loopt u naar uw verblijf.  Langs het pad staan allemaal fruit struiken, maar die moeten nog een beetje groeien.
U komt nu aan bij een klein trapje met 5 treden. U stapt nu op het terras en ziet het eerste doorkijkje naar het mooie uitzicht.

Via de openslaande deuren komt u uw verblijf binnen. Hier ziet u twee 1 persoonsbedden. Overdag heerlijk als bank en 's avonds een comfortabel bed. Aan 1 kant van de bedden zitten wielen, waardoor ze makkelijk tegen elkaar aan te zetten zijn.
Boven het raam ziet u een brede plank. Hierop kunt u uw kleren en koffers kwijt.
Vanaf de bank kijkt u door dit raam op oog hoogte zo het bos in. Misschien komt de eekhoorn nog wel even buurten. Of ziet u de reeën in het bos.

The Cabin offers true Muskoka scenery. This is a view from the outhouse looking back at the cabin.
The cabin offers great floor space for a couple or small family. The vaulted ceilings keep the space feeling open and bright.
The waterfront is as peaceful as it gets. There is a  dedicated waterfront at a small bay. The water is deep and weed free for perfect swimming. There is a canoe and paddle board for guest use.
Looking down river at the mouth to Pickerel lake. There is only one other dock within eyesight.
Relax in the screened in porch. The view is pretty and the birds sound amazing!
The main floor bedroom is cozy, comfortable and full of character.

The cabin has an upper loft which is 5' 10" at it's peak.  The view is lovely and guests have commented that 'It's like sleeping in a tree house." There is a queen, twin and double bed in the loft. We ask that the trap door remains closed for safety.
The loft queen bed is very comfortable.
A drop leaf table allows for a dining spot when eating inside. There is a picnic table outside.
The kitchen is functional and offers anything needed for simple meals including a fridge, microwave, kettle, coffee maker, crock pot, skillet,  salad spinner, strainer, all dishware and cutlery.
Living room and loft. The main floor bedroom can be seen to the right and the door to the screened in porch is to the left. The loft stairs are 'ladder like' with hand grips.
The outdoor shower has a sheltered sitting / change area.
The outdoor shower has on- demand heated water and is Instagram worthy!
A peek-a-boo wall  allows for a full forest view when showering! It closes for those who prefer privacy.
The side view of the cabin
The cabin is perched high in some beautify Muskoka scenery. The trail to the new waterfront includes a set  of stairs winding alongside a rock face.
The stairs to the new waterfront- from above.  The forested trail from the cabin to the waterfront is about 400ft.
The outhouse is clean and stocked with TP and hand wipes.
